snagit is a simple screen capture software that allows you to capture either videos or pictures of your desktop, edit, and share quickly. snagit also has a large library of drawing tools that allows you to grab your audience's attention with shapes, callouts, highlighting, step-by-step labels, and much more. some common uses of snagit include: it is very important to keep accessibility in mind when using snagit to ensure that all images whether placed on the web, word documents, or pdf files are accessible by including an alternative text (or alt text). alternative text provides users the ability to have a text description of what an image is showing. feel free to visit the websites below which will provide additional information about alternative text and how to apply alternative texts to microsoft word and pdf files. please use the on-demand video request form to request an introduction to snagit tutorial video or an advanced snagit features video. feel free to reach out to ecampus@sjsu.edu for any questions or assistance after viewing the on-demand videos. please fill out the snagit request form below if you would like to receive a copy of snagit. download adobe reader phone: 408-924-2337 email: ecampus@sjsu.edu location: irc, room 206 ecampus, irc206 instructional resource center san jose state university one washington square san jose, ca 95192-0026 